                  <handDesc>
          <handNote xml:id="h1" script="Ethiopic">
          <seg type="rubrication">
          <foreign xml:lang="gez">ኢግዚአብሔር፡</foreign>
          </seg>
          <desc>Columetric rubrication is employed only in the tenth biblical canticle</desc>
          </handNote>
          </handDesc>
          <decoDesc>
            <decoNote xml:id="d1">
              <locus target="#5r #11r #17v #24v #34r #41r #46r #54r #63v #70v #76r #100r #206r #112r" facs="005 011 018 025 034 041 046 054 064 071 076 100 206 112">Fols. 5r, 11r, 17v, 24v, 34r, 41r, 46r, 54r, 63v, 70v, 76r, 100r, 206r, 112r</locus>
              <desc>Ornamental designs</desc>
            </decoNote>
          </decoDesc>
          <additions>
          <list>
            <item xml:id="e1">
            <desc>Navigation system: Brown and green threads have been sewn into the fore edge of many folios in the book to mark the location of content</desc>
            </item>
            <item xml:id="e2">
            <locus target="#59r" facs="059">Fol. 59r</locus>
            <desc>The midpoint of the Psalms is marked with an indentation of the line and a small harag in line with the left margin</desc>
            </item>
            <item xml:id="a1">
            <locus target="#129v" facs="130">Fol. 129v</locus>
            <desc>
            The name <foreign xml:lang="gez">ወለተ ጽዮን</foreign>, Walatta Tsion (owner?) appears at the conclusion of the Song of Songs
            </desc>
            </item>
            <item xml:id="a2">
            <locus target="#130r" facs="130">Fol. 130r</locus>
            <desc>
            The Praises of Mary are laid out beginning on Monday and culminating on Sunday
            </desc>
            </item>
            <item xml:id="a3">
            <locus target="#145r" facs="145">Fol. 145r</locus>
            <desc type="OwnershipNote">
            Secondary note of ownership, <foreign xml:lang="gez">ዝዳዊት የእመት ዘነበች</foreign>
            </desc>
            </item>
            <item xml:id="a4">
            <locus target="#145v" facs="146">Fol. 145v</locus>
            <desc>
            Colophon, deleted
            </desc>
            </item>
            <item xml:id="e3">
            <locus target="#146v" facs="147">Fol. 146v</locus>
            <desc>
            The headband is comprised of braided red and green leather strips
            </desc>
            </item>
            <item xml:id="e4">
            <desc>
            This entry employs some information from Macomber, William F. “Catalogue of oriental manuscripts in the library of Seabury-Western Theological Seminary, Evanston, Illinois.” Le Muséon 92 (1979) 369–386
            </desc>
            </item>
          </list>
        </additions>
        <bindingDesc>
          <binding xml:id="binding" contemporary="true">
            <decoNote xml:id="b1">Parchment. Wooden boards carefully covered by tooled Moroccan leather. Beautiful fabric is visible between the turndowns for both front and back inside covers.</decoNote>
            <decoNote xml:id="b2" type="bindingMaterial">
              <material key="parchment"/>
              <material key="wood"/>
              <material key="leather"/>
              <material key="textile"/>
            </decoNote>
          </binding>
        </bindingDesc>
